The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | OCA boss speaks for India
                                                   OCA boss speaks for India
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The president of the Olympic Council of Asia (OCA), Sheikh Ahmad Al-Fahad Al-Sabah Wednesday said India was a safe country and that it should have the chance to host the Asian Games in 2018.         
	The OCA chief, who was here to meet Indian Olympic Association (IOA) officials, said there were no security concerns in India.         
	We are friends of India. Its our duty to send the message everywhere that India is as secure as anywhere else in the world. This is the right time The Asian sports members should go hand in hand. We trust the security and leadership of the country, he said.         
	India, the OCA president said, has had the experience of hosting the inaugural Games in 1951 and then in 1982, and is also going to stage the Commonwealth Games next year.         
	The country has changed a lot and they should get the chance to host the Games with new technology in a new atmosphere, Al-Sabah said.                                                                                                                       
